[h3 id=Stage-by-Stagecomments: 
	" Stage-by-Stage comments:
	$LF
]h3
[h3 id=Metalman 
	" Metalman
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"By avoiding the floor cleaner we are able to damage boost through one of the moles instead of the falling-hammer and manipulate the RNG so that the next mole will drop a big health refill.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Rest of the Stage is unchanged.
	$LF
]p
[h3 id=Woodman 
	" Woodman
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"Nothing in the Stage has changed, except small improvements.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"To describe the Woodshield one would say: "A shoe too large trips one up" - normally it should keep sprites out, but there are so many openings Megaman just has to fill them with metalblades.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[small 
		"sidenote Megaman loves to shot like a Shotgun in all directions :^) 
	]small
	$LF
]p
[h3 id=Airman 
	" Airman
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"Nothing big changed..
	$LF
]p
[h3 id=Clashman 
	" Clashman
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"The start of the stage is identically to the old run, before the long fall it is indeed faster to shot the can-guy and slide all the way.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Clash fight is 
	[b 
		"worth
	]b
	" watching! You may not notice it but Megaman does a slide in mid-air because of bad programming.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"The right side of the screen, somehow, behaves like a blackhole. All sprites (clouds from the airshooter) that leave to the right are instantly gone and thus enable Megaman to hit Clashman faster.
	$LF
]p
[h3 id=Magnetman 
	" Magnetman
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"With good RNG a big health-refill has been dropped by one of the enemies giving Megaman the ability to slide through the last enemy before the bossdoor.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"In the middle of the Stage those magnetic-zones which pull Megaman to the right are abused to get a little bit faster through the long hallway.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Magnetman fight is unchanged..
	$LF
]p
[h3 id=Hardman 
	" Hardman
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"Nothing big changed, again..
	$LF
]p
[h3 id=Topman 
	" Topman
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"Now it's getting interesting, Megaman equipped with the Infinity Gauntlet blazes through the game and nothing is able stop him..
	$LF
]p
[h3 id=Needleman 
	" Needleman
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"By sacrificing some minor frames 
	[small 
		"collecting refills
	]small
	" Megaman is able to save even more in the long run 
	[small 
		"the pathway with all those damn needles which run on a global timer..
	]small
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"After seeing Megamans dance moves Needleman decided to detonate and at least try to hit Megaman with some particles but to no avail..
	$LF
]p
[h3 id=Quint 
	" Quint
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"Figured out that Sakugarne
	[small 
		"the pogostick
	]small
	" has a fixed appearance after 128 frames, with this knowledge Megaman can take his time and divest himself of Quint
	[small 
		"his older?/younger?-brother
	]small
	" by 8 shots from the buster and 4 precise punches from the Infinity Gauntlet 
	[small 
		"Quint has 32 HP - hardknuckle deals 6, clashbomb 4, other weapons 2, buster 1
	]small
	$LF
]p
[h3 id=Wily 
	" Wily
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"After the loss of his brother Megaman seeks revenge and hops into 
	[del 
		"Rushmarine
	]del
	" 
	[del 
		"Rushjet
	]del
	" 
	[b 
		"Rushmissile âœ”
	]b
	" and hunts down the nasty old Dr.Wily
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Using every last drop of strength, Megaman awakens his ability to make an airjump by clenching his fist with the Infinity Gauntlet 
	[small 
		"this avoids going to the menu or waiting for those platforms to appear
	]small
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Using Sakugarne 
	[small 
		"the pogostick
	]small
	" is -to my astonishment- faster then using buster, as a nice gimmick Megaman doesn't even have to change back to buster.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"After the fight, Dr.Wily tries to escape to another galaxy but 
	[b 
		"one
	]b
	" little snap with the Infinity Gauntlet makes him disappear..
	$LF
]p
